  <exercise>
    <introduction>
      <p>Consider the voting system <m>[25 | 24, 20, 1]</m>.</p>
    </introduction>
    <task xml:id="voting-banzhaf-homework1">
      <statement>
        <p>Calculate the percentage of the total weight that each voter holds.</p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>53.3%, 44.4%, 2.2%</p>
      </answer>
    </task>
    <task xml:id="voting-banshaf-homework2">
      <statement>
        <p>Calculate the Banzhaf Power Index for each voter.</p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>0.60, 0.20, 0.20</p>
      </answer>
    </task>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Comparing your answers to parts <xref ref="voting-banzhaf-homework1" text="local"/> and <xref ref="voting-banshaf-homework2" text="local"/>, explain in complete sentences
          why the weight controlled by the voter is not the same thing as the power held by each voter.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          For example, voter <m>P_2</m> has twenty times more weight than voter <m>P_3</m>,
          but they have exactly the same power.
          Another way to see it is that voter <m>P_1</m> has three times as much power as voter <m>P_2</m>,
          even though the weights of 24 and 20 are not that different.
        </p>
      </solution>
    </task>
  </exercise>

