  <exercise>
    <title>Nassau County Board of Supervisors</title>
    
    
    <introduction>
      <p>
        Nassau County, New York used to be governed by a Board of Supervisors.
        The county had six districts, each of which sent one delegate to vote on county issues.
        The delegates' votes were weighted proportionately to the districts' population in 1964:
      </p>
      <tabular halign="center">
        <row bottom="medium">
          <cell left="medium" right="medium">District</cell>
          <cell right="medium">Weight</cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell left="medium" right="medium">Hempstead #1</cell>
          <cell right="medium">31</cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell left="medium" right="medium">Hempstead #2</cell>
          <cell right="medium">31</cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell left="medium" right="medium">Oyster Bay</cell>
          <cell right="medium">28</cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell left="medium" right="medium">North Hempstead</cell>
          <cell right="medium">21</cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell left="medium" right="medium">Long Beach</cell>
          <cell right="medium">2</cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell left="medium" right="medium">Glen Cove</cell>
          <cell right="medium">2</cell>
        </row>
      </tabular>
      <p>A simple majority was needed to pass a motion.</p>
    </introduction>

    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>Express this weighted voting system in our usual notation.</p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p><m>[58 | 31, 31, 28, 21, 2, 2]</m></p>
